ding to some commentators; others construe the clause 'at a\nvery low price' with each part of the sentence.\n\n[350:6](sbe3376.htm#fr_1139) Viv. p. 116; Col. Dig. III, 3, 14; May. p. 131.\n'Within that period,' i.e. the period allowed for examination.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: XIX. Boundary Disputes](sbe3377.htm)\n\n"